6. Conclusion & Mitigations
XSLT Security: Always disable the use of external entities and dangerous extensions like exslt:document in your XSLT processor.

Password Hashing: Move away from MD5. Use robust, salted algorithms like Argon2 or BCrypt.

Patch Management: Regularly update system utilities like needrestart to patch known privilege escalation vulnerabilities.
